msgid ""
"This is a convenience function for users porting code from Matlab, and wraps "
"`random_sample`. That function takes a tuple to specify the size of the "
"output, which is consistent with other NumPy functions like `numpy.zeros` "
"and `numpy.ones`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/random/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.random.RandomState.rand:10
msgid ""
"Create an array of the given shape and populate it with random samples from "
"a uniform distribution over ``[0, 1)``."
msgstr ""

